THE KZN transport MEC, Peggy Nkonyeni, was involved in a car accident on her way to launch a youth economic empowerment programme. The programme will see more than 4 000 young people employed by the Department of Transport. It is said that the accident happened on the R66 road in Ulundi, northern KZN, on Tuesday, 21 June. Nkonyeni was returning from an engagement with Premier Sihle Zikalala and King Misuzulu. Zikalala was among the first people who arrived at the accident scene He said Nkonyeni and her close protectors were involved in the accident after a tyre burst. Zikalala along with the director-general Dr Nonhlanhla Mkhize ensured that the MEC and her protectors were helped and that they received urgent medical care. “MEC Nkonyeni was involved in an accident just after we had concluded a very fruitful engagement with His Majesty the King Misuzulu kaZwelithini to get the king’s guidance on various pertinent matters in the province. “Nkonyeni is currently undergoing complete medical evaluation. She is fully conscious and alert. On behalf of the people and government of KwaZulu-Natal, we wish Nkonyeni and her protectors a speedy recovery,” said Zikalala. Zikalala assured the people of KZN that the MEC and her protectors were receiving the best medical attention.